Program: Outlook
Title: The Syrian internet activist persecuted by the secret police and forced to leave his homeland
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00y7fwy
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 27 Sep 2012
An interview with Syrian activist Rami Nakhla who was persecuted by the secret police and forced into exile. Also, British writer Patrick McGrath on the influence of a childhood next door to a high security hospital for the criminally insane. And John Mpaliza from Congo, who walked 1600 kilometres to raise awareness of the suffering of his people. Show less